%I A394516 #15 Jun 22 2026 23:00:09
%S A394516 0,1,1,6,69,1050,20025,464310,12709305,401112810,14338565325,
%T A394516 572611173750,25266579878925,1220800994062650,64103611995648225,
%U A394516 3634857586199589750,221351219713825826625,14408019726213777914250,998273842698610388035125,73354211365735687418781750
%N A394516 Number of rooted binary time-consistent leaf-labeled galled trees with n leaves.
%C A394516 Also the number of rooted binary normal leaf-labeled galled trees with n leaves.
%H A394516 Lily Agranat-Tamir, Michael Fuchs, Bernhard Gittenberger, and Noah A. Rosenberg, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.tcs.2026.116075">Enumerative combinatorics of unlabeled and labeled time-consistent galled trees</a>, Theor. Comp. Sci. 1082 (2026), 116075. See Table 5.
%F A394516 E.g.f. satisfies A(x) = x + (1/2)*A(x)^2 + (1/2)*A(x)*(A(x)/(1-A(x)))^2.
%e A394516 For n=3 leaves, there are 3 rooted binary leaf-labeled trees with three leaves and no galls: ((A,B),C), ((A,C),B), and ((B,C),A). There are 3 rooted binary leaf-labaled trees with a root gall from which three leaves are descended, one each for the  three distinct labels that can descend from the reticulation node. Hence, a(3)=3+3=6.
%t A394516 terms = 20; A[_] = 0; Do[A[x_] = x + (1/2)*A[x]^2 + (1/2)*A[x]*(A[x]/(1-A[x]))^2 + O[x]^terms // Normal, terms]; CoefficientList[A[x], x]*Range[0,terms-1]! (* _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 18 2026 *)
%Y A394516 Cf. A001147 (rooted binary leaf-labeled trees with n leaves and 0 galls), A396954 (rooted binary time-consistent leaf-labeled galled trees with n leaves and 1 gall), A380211 (rooted binary time-consistent unlabeled galled trees with n leaves).
%K A394516 nonn,new
%O A394516 0,4
%A A394516 _Noah A Rosenberg_, Jun 18 2026
%E A394516 Data corrected by _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 18 2026
